Real attack Scenario: 

procdump.exe -ma lsass.exe
↓
Extract passwords
↓
Move laterally

Tools like Mimikatz, ProcDump (procdump.exe -ma lsass.exe lsass.dmp, abusing a legitimate Microsoft signed tool), or the built-in comsvcs.dll MiniDump technique are used by attackers who've already landed on a box, to steal credentials and move laterally to other machines using those stolen hashes (Pass-the-Hash). This is a textbook step between "initial foothold" and "domain admin."